calculator_protocols[3]{id,protocol_name,targets,when_to_use,how_it_works,keystroke_sequence,failure_mode,recovery}:
  1,"ANS Loop (Recursive Substitution)",1.2;1.3,"Finding converged roots for iteration (cubic EOS vapor/liquid; virial volume)","Seed initial guess, program formula using ANS as variable, press = repeatedly until number stabilizes (convergence = first 2 decimals freeze)","Seed: 3076.9 → = | Program: [formula with ANS] | Press = iteratively (5-12 times) | Read final value","M+ contamination: Adding new root to old root instead of replacing. Causes denominator to inflate wildly (false spike to 500+)","NEVER mix with M+. If numbers diverge: Clear calculator, re-type ANS loop formula exactly, start over with correct initial guess."
  2,"M+ Memory Vault (Chunk Assembly)",1.1;1.3,"Adding mathematical fragments without bracket syntax errors (polynomial integration, work assembly)","Calculate single block, press M+ to store. Calculate next block, press M+. Finally press RCL M+ to extract sum.","Block 1: [calc] → M+ | Block 2: [calc] → M+ | Block 3: [calc] → M+ | RCL M+ (reads sum) | MR (clears memory)","Pressing = instead of M+: Causes calculator to REPLACE memory instead of ADD to it. Only last block is retained.","After each M+, verify you see 'M' indicator on screen. Before final RCL M+, press 0 + M+ to ensure memory is initialized clean."
  3,"2000-Divisor Unit Trap",2.1,"Converting kinetic energy from J/kg to kJ/kg within SFEE formula (velocity in m/s → thermodynamic equation in kJ)","Pre-bake unit conversion into the fraction: use 2000 in denominator instead of 2. Formula: ΔH + (u₂²-u₁²)/2000 = Q + Ws","Direct: (700² - 0²) / 2000 → (490000 / 2000) → 245 kJ/kg","Dividing by 2 alone: Kinetic energy becomes 1000× too large, destroying SFEE balance. Or dividing by 1000 alone: Forgets the 1/2 from kinetic formula.","Always write 2000, never 2 or 1000. Verify: If your kinetic term is >50% of enthalpy/work magnitude, you likely divided by 2."

