PROTOCOL INTERACTION MATRIX:
----------------------------
Which protocol for each target?

Target 1.1 (Sensible Heat): M+ ONLY (3 blocks → sum)
Target 1.2 (Cubic EOS): ANS ONLY (vapor iteration, then liquid iteration)
Target 1.3 (Virial Work): ANS (for V₂ iteration) THEN M+ (for 3-chunk assembly)
Target 2.1 (SFEE): 2000-Divisor ONLY (direct arithmetic, no looping)
Target 2.2 (PV Matrix): Standard algebra (no special protocol)
Target 2.3 (Derivation): N/A (theory question, no calculator)

⚠️ CRITICAL RULE: NEVER MIX PROTOCOLS
----
ANS + M+ = CATASTROPHE (runaway sum in iterative loop)
M+ + ANS = CATASTROPHE (memory corruption in recursion)
2000 + 2 = FAILURE (unit trap nullified)

---
CASIO FX-82MS SPECIFIC LIMITATIONS & WORKAROUNDS:
-------------------------------------------------
Limitation 1: No Natural Display (no fraction rendering)
Workaround: Use Chunking Protocol to break massive expressions into bite-sized parts

Limitation 2: No Auto-Integration (no ∫ dx button)
Workaround: Pre-integrate formula mathematically on paper, use calculator only for arithmetic

Limitation 3: Limited Bracket Nesting (max 18 opening brackets)
Workaround: Calculate largest terms first, use M+ to store, assemble at end

Limitation 4: No memory for formulas (can't save equation strings)
Workaround: Memorize the exact ANS loop sequence; drill until muscle memory replaces reading

---
KEYSTROKE DRILL SEQUENCES:

SEQUENCE 1: ANS Loop for Vapor Root (Target 1.2, n=5 iterations)
Step 1: [3076.9] [=]                                          (seed: V₀)
Step 2: [3076.9] [+] [80.67] [-] [(] [16186981] [÷] [9.4573] [)] [×] (setup)
Step 3: [ANS] [(] [ANS] [+] [80.67] [)] [÷] [ANS] [×] [ANS] [+] [80.67] [=]
Step 4: [=] [=] [=] [=] [=]                                  (iterations 1-5)
Final: Read V_vapor on display (should stabilize ~2447.6 cm³/mol)

SEQUENCE 2: M+ Chunking for Sensible Heat (Target 1.1, 3 blocks)
Step 1: [Block_1_calc] [M+]                                   (T difference term)
Step 2: [Block_2_calc] [M+]                                   (T² difference term)
Step 3: [Block_3_calc] [M+]                                   (T³ or 1/T term)
Step 4: [RCL] [M+] or [RCL] [M]                               (read sum)
Step 5: [×] [8.314] [=]                                       (multiply by R)
Final: Read ΔH on display (should be in J/mol range: 6000-17000)

SEQUENCE 3: 2000-Divisor Direct Calc (Target 2.1)
Step 1: [(] [700] [x²] [-] [0] [x²] [)] [÷] [2000] [=]      (kinetic energy)
Step 2: [+] [0] [+] [280] [=]                                 (SFEE assembly)
Step 3: [AC] (clear) [Ans] [-] [280] [=]                      (solve for Q)
Final: Read Q (should be around -35 to +200 kJ/kg depending on process)

---
ERROR RECOVERY PROTOCOL:
------------------------
If ANS Loop Shows Wild Oscillation (e.g., 500+, then 100, then 5000):
→ You have mixed ANS + M+ protocols
→ Clear memory: [MC] or [Del]
→ Restart ANS loop with fresh initial guess
→ Do NOT attempt to salvage calculation

If M+ Vault Shows Only Last Block Value:
→ You pressed [=] instead of [M+]
→ Clear memory: [MC]
→ Recalculate all 3 blocks, pressing M+ after EACH
→ Verify 'M' appears on screen after each M+

If 2000-Divisor Gives Kinetic Energy > Enthalpy:
→ You divided by 2 or 1000, not 2000
→ Redo: (700² - 0²) = 490000 → ÷ 2000 = 245 (correct)
→ If you got 245000 or 24500, wrong divisor was used

